Servants of Saruman x 3    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Bid 6 and pull Aragorn (a.k.a. &quot;Medicinal Herbs&quot;).  Aragorn not only is a killer companion, but he&#39;s such a good friend he&#39;ll spot you the weed for free from time to time...  When the secret stash is empty it&#39;s time to call uncle Bilbo, who&#39;s got the MAD hookups baby!  With his good friend Elrond, he&#39;ll supply you whatever you need from the special Rivendell hydroponics station...  Galadriel can take the heat off Elrond or even your good bud-dy Legolas (a.k.a &quot;the light weight&quot;).  Filbert&#39;s got your back when the credit card company&#39;s realize you aren&#39;t planning to pay the bills.  You may think it&#39;s time to lay back and enjoy, but first you got&#39;s to give your good friend Gandalf (a.k.a. &quot;the chimney&quot;) and hell... while we are partying, might as well invite Jerry and the rest of the dead (a.k.a. Saruman and them gosh darnit Isengard Orcs) to help down this big bag of herbs.<br />
<br />
Anyways... you get the point.  Heal with the herbs, kill whatever you can in archery, heal with herbs, recycle herbs with Bilbo, heal Bilbo with Frodo and Bilbo, and draw tons of cards w/ Elrond, Old Toby and Abandoning Reason for madness.<br />
<br />
Card Choices not already &quot;explained&quot;:<br />
ARV: because it&#39;s still good and I hate early Witch Kings...<br />
The Gaffer&#39;s Pipe:  a good 4th pipe, also plays on either Bilbo or Filibert. (Note: Elrond should really get a pipe... I can tell his eyes are a little bloodshot... he loves the sweet cheeba!)<br />
Betrayal of Isengard:  to stop T.J. Hooker (a.k.a. Saruman) from ruining the party<br />
Balrog: anyone need a light? :)<br />
Saruman x 4:  Best minion in an Isengard Orc deck... essential.<br />
Wizard Storm & A Fell Voice: SOOO good in this deck.  Yes... it works... I think.<br />
Enquea: Someone&#39;s gotta finish the job...<br />
Can You Protect Me From Yourself: Enquea power and because it just fits well into the deck.  Easily played as well. &quot;Don&#39;t let the man get ya down.&quot;<br />
Servants of Saruman: Don&#39;t let them fool you, winning skirmishes with IsenOrcs IS important...<br />
<br />
Thanks for your comments and reviews.  Remember that life is about having fun, so don&#39;t take your decks or any GAME too seriously!<br />
